                            <comment id="12982341" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Sun, 16 Jan 2011 17:17:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Glen, how do you run this example in CXF ? Are you sure you haven&apos;t specified NotFoundExceptionMapper as a service bean ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12982357" author="gmazza" created="Sun, 16 Jan 2011 18:44:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Instructions for running the example are in the last sentence of the description.  NotFoundExceptionMapper is as given in the description, and linked in as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class ShoppingApplication extends Application&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
   private Set&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt; singletons = new HashSet&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt;();&lt;br/&gt;
   private Set&amp;lt;Class&amp;lt;?&amp;gt;&amp;gt; classes = new HashSet&amp;lt;Class&amp;lt;?&amp;gt;&amp;gt;();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   public ShoppingApplication()&lt;/p&gt;
   {
      singletons.add(new CustomerResource());
      classes.add(NotFoundExceptionMapper.class);
   }

&lt;p&gt;   ...&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12982361" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Sun, 16 Jan 2011 18:54:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Application.getClasses() can also return provider classes, not only root resource classes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
